      • setSize

        public PrivilegeChecksTypes.IterationSpec.Builder setSize(java.lang.Long size)
        Specifies the maximum number of results to return. This property was added in vSphere API 8.0.0.0. If null defaults to default page size, which is controlled by config.vpxd.privilegeChecks.pageSize advanced option.
        Parameters:
        size - New value for the property.

      • setMarker

        public PrivilegeChecksTypes.IterationSpec.Builder setMarker(java.lang.String marker)
        An opaque token which determines where the returned page should begin. This property was added in vSphere API 8.0.0.0. If null or empty, privilege checks will be returned from the first record.
        Parameters:
        marker - New value for the property.

      • setEndMarker

        public PrivilegeChecksTypes.IterationSpec.Builder setEndMarker(java.lang.String endMarker)
        An opaque token which determines where the returned page should end. This property was added in vSphere API 8.0.0.0. If null or empty, privilege checks will be returned up to size, if set, or up to the default page size.
        Parameters:
        endMarker - New value for the property.

      • setTimeoutMs

        public PrivilegeChecksTypes.IterationSpec.Builder setTimeoutMs(java.lang.Long timeoutMs)
        Indicates how long the request should wait in ms for a matching check if PrivilegeChecksTypes.IterationSpec.getMarker() is set, and there no matching checks to be added to the result. This property was added in vSphere API 8.0.0.0. If null or empty, the request will not wait for additional privilege checks and will return immediately.
        Parameters:
        timeoutMs - New value for the property.
